he only one in the zone.  When I was the only one there (at level 57) I could keep the hall clear down to the fort by myself.  By the time I had the last part of the left hall killed, there was respawn up top.  Reasonable, no?  All right, so this 59 SK shows up with his primal 2hander and spiffy black armor.  He pulls a couple mobs from the zonein while I am medding, and kills them in about 30 seconds each.  It takes me well over that much time to kill a chardok mob solo, and then I have down time...He didn't have any.  Snare, fear, double for 300+ about once a second....That's damage, not doubling for 60 with the occasional tripple or quad...come ON.  He proceeded to clear the entire zoneout and, with a click of his pegasus cloak, lev'ed up into the left tunnel...He popped out of the empty fort about half an hour later, and we were still the only two in the zone.  /boggle.  So, YOU tell ME...are melee's overpowered, in that they can rip through a 50+ zone with no downtime and put out well over 100 DPS while tanking the mobs and taking hits in sub-50 range?  Or are mages overpowered, along with the rest of us poor casters, in that our PEAK output damage barely matches that of a single shadow knight in good gear, and that he can keep it up without a pause while we need to med for MUCH longer than it takes us to do the damage?  That is when I decided I wasn't too interested in playing a mage any more.  I like to feel Useful (tm).  In order to do that, I must do one of several things: I must contribute significant damage to a mob, or I must provide some uncomparable service to the group or raid.  Since on TM there is no shortage of Enlightened Dark or Clan of Shadows or Enrapture melee's and clerics, doing a group damage equivilant to 15 mages and pulling trains because the mobs pretty much just can't hurt them...Everquest has become seriously unbalanced, and Verant KNOWS that they can't nerf melee...they'd lose players.  They also KNOW that they can't bring casters up to the DPS and easy of fighting that melee have at this point, then the game would be TWICE as unbalanced.  They'd have to re-evaluate all the planes and endgame encounters, they'd have to put in new harder zones which would be ignored by groups who went back to kunark and old world zones to solo entire dungeons...Here we go, I'm doomscrying the end...Everquest isn't going to last another three years, I'd stake a fair wager on that.<br>
