 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uorbittm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OrbitTM</A> at: 1/23/02 7:06:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unovinthemagician.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Novin the Magician</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/02 7:34:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=73>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We need to STOP this.</span><hr size=1> Very interesting post, my take on things is:<br>
<br>
We're *ok* right now, but we do need improvement.  Our primary role as a support class (and don't be mistaken, in the end-game environment that *is* our role) does work, albeit very constrictively (COH and only a few conjures are our valued presence, pets are not)  There are only a couple of issues that I think really *need* to be worked on, then a couple which I feel would be *nice*  In general though, I totally agree with the post's intent:  We do need to be constructive and analytical in our presentation of needed improvements and modifications, and not to come off as &quot;whining&quot;, because as someone said, you can very well just &quot;say&quot; that virtually anything is unbalanced, unfair, or in need of change - proving it as a priority over something else is the hard part.<br>
<br>
Needs:<br>
<br>
1. Pathing improvements.  Our pets are great, but the fact is that, due to pathing and command interface it's almost criminal to try using them in a very extreme number of environments (easily half the places in game are marked &quot;unsafe&quot; for pets)  The new Luclin command /pet Hold as implemented as a costly class skill I consider a slap in the face - Mages are the only ones who *need* that due to our reliance on pets and it should have been issued to us, and for free, a long long time ago - not as a 6-level Class skill cost.<br>
<br>
2. Damage relativity update.  Druids SHOULD NOT overnuke a Mage, period.  I asked bluntly the ratio on the best Druid DD vs. my best (and mind you NEW Luclin DD), and found out that the Druid one is more powerful in EVERY way (Cast speed, manacost, and dmg amount)<br>
<br>
<br>
Would be nice:<br>
<br>
1.  More conjures.  Hey, every time someone asks me why I picked being a Mage, I answer as follows:  &quot;I love to conjure up cool crap and blow things up.&quot;  Basically, as long as I'm highly capable of those 2 things I'm a happy Magi <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   That being said, we sure could use a bunch more useful conjures... we have many that are useful, but as someone stated already the implementation of some of them into item right-clicks for other classes lowers their value so we should have more alternatives to compensate and keep us with a vast, not limited, variety of conjurables.<br>
<br>
2.  Pet modes.  As masters of pets, moreso than other classes, I feel it would be good if we had better control of our pet's/preferances than we do.  For instance, the fact that there is almost no functional difference between my pet being in Taunting mode versus it not being in taunting mode bothers me.  Also as stated with the /pet hold, that's an insult - that should be free, and if we had to pay exp for anything it should be an alternate combat mode entirely (like &quot;/pet guard target&quot; to provide that the pet defends another player as it would otherwise defend its Master... I've always dreamed of having that one *drool*) <p>Novin, 60 Arch Mage
Server: Eci
Guild: Arete

Craziest Mage in all of Norrath (and now Luclin)  Master of Factional knowledge (if I'm not nonKOS to it, it's because it either isn't possible or I don't care)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/02 9:19:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=74>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We will NEVER be as strong as we was pre-kunark.. Your another one that lives in the past and dont want to see the good in our class..<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
